{"word":"H170 - אׇהֳלָה - ʼOhŏlâh - o-hol-aw' - Aholah","slug":"H170","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">אׇהֳלָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʼOhŏlâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>o-hol-aw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Aholah"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>אהלהּ אהלה</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>'ohŏlâh 'ohŏlâhh</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>o-hol-aw'</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> Aholah = \"her own tent\" <ol><li>Samaria as an adulteress with Assyria (metaphorically)</li></ol> <p />Origin: in form a f of <a href=\"#/H168\">H168</a>, but in fact for 'Oholahh o-hol-aw' <p />TWOT entry: <a class=\"T\" href=\"S:0032 - 'ahal\">32b</a> <p />Part(s) of speech: Proper Name Feminine "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H167\">H167</a>, <a href=\"#/H168\">H168</a>, <a href=\"#/H169\">H169</a>, <a href=\"#/H171\">H171</a>, <a href=\"#/H172\">H172</a>, <a href=\"#/H173\">H173</a>"}]}